OpenAI API

API and SDK Documentation

Version: 2.0.0
The OpenAI REST API. Please see https://platform.openai.com/docs/api-reference for more details.

Assistants

cancelRun

Cancels a run that is `in_progress`.


/threads/{thread_id}/runs/{run_id}/cancel

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Dart
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
  • Rust
curl -X POST \
 -H "Authorization: Bearer [[accessToken]]" \
 -H "Accept: application/json" \
 "https://api.openai.com/v1/threads/{thread_id}/runs/{run_id}/cancel"

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.AssistantsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class AssistantsApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        AssistantsApi apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();
        String threadId = threadId_example; // String | The ID of the thread to which this run belongs.
        String runId = runId_example; // String | The ID of the run to cancel.

        try {
            RunObject result = apiInstance.cancelRun(threadId, runId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling AssistantsApi#cancelRun");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

public class AssistantsApiExample {

        String runId = runId_example; // String | The ID of the run to cancel.

        try {
            RunObject result = apiInstance.cancelRun(threadId, runId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling AssistantsApi#cancelRun");
            e.printStackTrace();

Configuration *apiConfig = [Configuration sharedConfig];

// Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
[apiConfig setAccessToken:@"YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN"];

// Create an instance of the API class
AssistantsApi *apiInstance = [[AssistantsApi alloc] init];
String *threadId = threadId_example; // The ID of the thread to which this run belongs. (default to null)
String *runId = runId_example; // The ID of the run to cancel. (default to null)

// Cancels a run that is `in_progress`.
[apiInstance cancelRunWith:threadId
    runId:runId
              completionHandler: ^(RunObject output, NSError* error) {
    if (output) {
        NSLog(@"%@", output);
    }
    if (error) {
        NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
    }
}];

var defaultClient = OpenAiApi.ApiClient.instance;

ApiKeyAuth.accessToken = "YOUR ACCESS TOKEN";

var api = new OpenAiApi.AssistantsApi()
var threadId = threadId_example; // {String} The ID of the thread to which this run belongs.
var runId = runId_example; // {String} The ID of the run to cancel.

var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.cancelRun(threadId, runId, callback);

using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Api;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Client;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class cancelRunExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
            Configuration.Default.AccessToken = "YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN";

            // Create an instance of the API class
            var apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();
            var threadId = threadId_example;  // String | The ID of the thread to which this run belongs. (default to null)
            var runId = runId_example;  // String | The ID of the run to cancel. (default to null)

            try {
                // Cancels a run that is `in_progress`.
                RunObject result = apiInstance.cancelRun(threadId, runId);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            } catch (Exception e) {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling AssistantsApi.cancelRun: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

from __future__ import print_statement
import time
import openapi_client
from openapi_client.rest import ApiException
from pprint import pprint

# Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
openapi_client.configuration.access_token = 'YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN'

# Create an instance of the API class
api_instance = openapi_client.AssistantsApi()
threadId = threadId_example # String | The ID of the thread to which this run belongs. (default to null)
runId = runId_example # String | The ID of the run to cancel. (default to null)

try:
    # Cancels a run that is `in_progress`.
    api_response = api_instance.cancel_run(threadId, runId)
    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:
    print("Exception when calling AssistantsApi->cancelRun: %s\n" % e)
extern crate AssistantsApi;

pub fn main() {
    let threadId = threadId_example; // String
    let runId = runId_example; // String

    let mut context = AssistantsApi::Context::default();
    let result = client.cancelRun(threadId, runId, &context).wait();

    println!("{:?}", result);
}

createAssistantFile

Create an assistant file by attaching a [File](/docs/api-reference/files) to an [assistant](/docs/api-reference/assistants).


/assistants/{assistant_id}/files

import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;

import org.openapitools.client.api.AssistantsApi;

import java.io.File;

public class AssistantsApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth

        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        AssistantsApi apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();
        String assistantId = file-abc123; // String | The ID of the assistant for which to create a File.

        CreateAssistantFileRequest createAssistantFileRequest = ; // CreateAssistantFileRequest | 

        try {
            AssistantFileObject result = apiInstance.createAssistantFile(assistantId, createAssistantFileRequest);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling AssistantsApi#createAssistantFile");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

 (default to null)

using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Api;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Client;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class createAssistantFileExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
            Configuration.Default.AccessToken = "YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN";

            // Create an instance of the API class
            var apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();
            var assistantId = file-abc123;  // String | The ID of the assistant for which to create a File.
 (default to null)
            var createAssistantFileRequest = new CreateAssistantFileRequest(); // CreateAssistantFileRequest | 

            try {
                // Create an assistant file by attaching a [File](/docs/api-reference/files) to an [assistant](/docs/api-reference/assistants).
                AssistantFileObject result = apiInstance.createAssistantFile(assistantId, createAssistantFileRequest);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            } catch (Exception e) {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling AssistantsApi.createAssistantFile: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

from __future__ import print_statement
import time
import openapi_client
from openapi_client.rest import ApiException
from pprint import pprint

# Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
openapi_client.configuration.access_token = 'YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN'

# Create an instance of the API class
api_instance = openapi_client.AssistantsApi()
threadId = threadId_example # String | The ID of the thread to delete. (default to null)

try:
    # Delete a thread.
    api_response = api_instance.delete_thread(threadId)
    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:
    print("Exception when calling AssistantsApi->deleteThread: %s\n" % e)
extern crate AssistantsApi;

pub fn main() {
    let threadId = threadId_example; // String

    let mut context = AssistantsApi::Context::default();
    let result = client.deleteThread(threadId, &context).wait();

    println!("{:?}", result);
}

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.AssistantsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class AssistantsApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        AssistantsApi apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();
        String assistantId = assistantId_example; // String | The ID of the assistant to retrieve.

        try {
            AssistantObject result = apiInstance.getAssistant(assistantId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling AssistantsApi#getAssistant");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

var OpenAiApi = require('open_ai_api');

var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.getAssistant(assistantId, callback);

        {

            Configuration.Default.AccessToken = "YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN";

            // Create an instance of the API class
            var apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();
            var assistantId = assistantId_example;  // String | The ID of the assistant to retrieve. (default to null)

            try {
                // Retrieves an assistant.

                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            } catch (Exception e) {

            }
        }
    }
}

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.AssistantsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class AssistantsApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        AssistantsApi apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();
        String assistantId = assistantId_example; // String | The ID of the assistant who the file belongs to.
        String fileId = fileId_example; // String | The ID of the file we're getting.

        try {
            AssistantFileObject result = apiInstance.getAssistantFile(assistantId, fileId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling AssistantsApi#getAssistantFile");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.AssistantsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class AssistantsApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        AssistantsApi apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();
        String threadId = threadId_example; // String | The ID of the [thread](/docs/api-reference/threads) to which this message belongs.
        String messageId = messageId_example; // String | The ID of the message to retrieve.

        try {
            MessageObject result = apiInstance.getMessage(threadId, messageId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling AssistantsApi#getMessage");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.AssistantsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class AssistantsApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        AssistantsApi apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();
        String threadId = thread_abc123; // String | The ID of the thread to which the message and File belong.

openapi_client.configuration.access_token = 'YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN'

# Create an instance of the API class
api_instance = openapi_client.AssistantsApi()
threadId = thread_abc123 # String | The ID of the thread to which the message and File belong. (default to null)
messageId = msg_abc123 # String | The ID of the message the file belongs to. (default to null)
fileId = file-abc123 # String | The ID of the file being retrieved. (default to null)

try:
    # Retrieves a message file.
    api_response = api_instance.get_message_file(threadId, messageId, fileId)
    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:
    print("Exception when calling AssistantsApi->getMessageFile: %s\n" % e)
extern crate AssistantsApi;

pub fn main() {
    let threadId = thread_abc123; // String
    let messageId = msg_abc123; // String
    let fileId = file-abc123; // String

    let mut context = AssistantsApi::Context::default();
    let result = client.getMessageFile(threadId, messageId, fileId, &context).wait();

    println!("{:?}", result);
}

    }
}

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        AssistantsApi apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();
        String threadId = threadId_example; // String | The ID of the thread to which the run and run step belongs.
        String runId = runId_example; // String | The ID of the run to which the run step belongs.
        String stepId = stepId_example; // String | The ID of the run step to retrieve.

        try {
            RunStepObject result = apiInstance.getRunStep(threadId, runId, stepId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling AssistantsApi#getRunStep");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import java.io.File;

public class AssistantsApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        AssistantsApi apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();
        String assistantId = assistantId_example; // String | The ID of the assistant the file belongs to.
        Integer limit = 56; // Integer | A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 100, and the default is 20.

        String order = order_example; // String | Sort order by the `created_at` timestamp of the objects. `asc` for ascending order and `desc` for descending order.

        String after = after_example; // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.

        String before = before_example; // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `before` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include before=obj_foo in order to fetch the previous page of the list.


        try {
            ListAssistantFilesResponse result = apiInstance.listAssistantFiles(assistantId, limit, order, after, before);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling AssistantsApi#listAssistantFiles");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

limit
Integer
A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 100, and the default is 20.
order
String
Sort order by the `created_at` timestamp of the objects. `asc` for ascending order and `desc` for descending order.
after
String
A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.
before
String
A cursor for use in pagination. `before` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include before=obj_foo in order to fetch the previous page of the list.

Returns a list of messages for a given thread.


/threads/{thread_id}/messages

        AssistantsApi apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();

        Integer limit = 56; // Integer | A limit on the number of objects to be returned. Limit can range between 1 and 100, and the default is 20.

        String order = order_example; // String | Sort order by the `created_at` timestamp of the objects. `asc` for ascending order and `desc` for descending order.

        String after = after_example; // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.

        String before = before_example; // String | A cursor for use in pagination. `before` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include before=obj_foo in order to fetch the previous page of the list.

        String runId = runId_example; // String | Filter messages by the run ID that generated them.

            ListMessagesResponse result = apiInstance.listMessages(threadId, limit, order, after, before, runId);

extern crate AssistantsApi;

pub fn main() {
    let threadId = threadId_example; // String
    let limit = 56; // Integer
    let order = order_example; // String
    let after = after_example; // String
    let before = before_example; // String
    let runId = runId_example; // String

    let mut context = AssistantsApi::Context::default();
    let result = client.listMessages(threadId, limit, order, after, before, runId, &context).wait();

    println!("{:?}", result);
}

limit
Integer

order
String
Sort order by the `created_at` timestamp of the objects. `asc` for ascending order and `desc` for descending order.
after
String
A cursor for use in pagination. `after` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include after=obj_foo in order to fetch the next page of the list.
before
String
A cursor for use in pagination. `before` is an object ID that defines your place in the list. For instance, if you make a list request and receive 100 objects, ending with obj_foo, your subsequent call can include before=obj_foo in order to fetch the previous page of the list.

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        AssistantsApi apiInstance = new AssistantsApi();
        String threadId = threadId_example; // String | The ID of the thread to which this message belongs.
        String messageId = messageId_example; // String | The ID of the message to modify.
        ModifyMessageRequest modifyMessageRequest = ; // ModifyMessageRequest | 

        try {
            MessageObject result = apiInstance.modifyMessage(threadId, messageId, modifyMessageRequest);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling AssistantsApi#modifyMessage");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Responses

submitToolOuputsToRun

When a run has the `status: "requires_action"` and `required_action.type` is `submit_tool_outputs`, this endpoint can be used to submit the outputs from the tool calls once they're all completed. All outputs must be submitted in a single request. 


/threads/{thread_id}/runs/{run_id}/submit_tool_outputs

 -H "Authorization: Bearer [[accessToken]]" \
 -H "Accept: application/json" \
 -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
 "https://api.openai.com/v1/threads/{thread_id}/runs/{run_id}/submit_tool_outputs" \
 -d '{
  "stream" : true,
  "tool_outputs" : [ {
    "output" : "output",
    "tool_call_id" : "tool_call_id"
  }, {
    "output" : "output",
    "tool_call_id" : "tool_call_id"
  } ]
}'

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.AudioApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class AudioApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        AudioApi apiInstance = new AudioApi();
        File file = BINARY_DATA_HERE; // File | The audio file object (not file name) to transcribe, in one of these formats: flac, mp3, mp4, mpeg, mpga, m4a, ogg, wav, or webm.

        CreateTranscriptionRequest_model model = ; // CreateTranscriptionRequest_model | 
        String language = language_example; // String | The language of the input audio. Supplying the input language in [ISO-639-1](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_ISO_639-1_codes) format will improve accuracy and latency.

        String prompt = prompt_example; // String | An optional text to guide the model's style or continue a previous audio segment. The [prompt](/docs/guides/speech-to-text/prompting) should match the audio language.

        String responseFormat = responseFormat_example; // String | The format of the transcript output, in one of these options: `json`, `text`, `srt`, `verbose_json`, or `vtt`.

        BigDecimal temperature = 8.14; // BigDecimal | The sampling temperature, between 0 and 1. Higher values like 0.8 will make the output more random, while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic. If set to 0, the model will use [log probability](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Log_probability) to automatically increase the temperature until certain thresholds are hit.

        array[String] timestampGranularitiesLeft_Square_BracketRight_Square_Bracket = ; // array[String] | The timestamp granularities to populate for this transcription. `response_format` must be set `verbose_json` to use timestamp granularities. Either or both of these options are supported: `word`, or `segment`. Note: There is no additional latency for segment timestamps, but generating word timestamps incurs additional latency.


        try {
            createTranscription_200_response result = apiInstance.createTranscription(file, model, language, prompt, responseFormat, temperature, timestampGranularitiesLeft_Square_BracketRight_Square_Bracket);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling AudioApi#createTranscription");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import 'package:openapi/api.dart';

final api_instance = DefaultApi();

final File file = new File(); // File | The audio file object (not file name) to transcribe, in one of these formats: flac, mp3, mp4, mpeg, mpga, m4a, ogg, wav, or webm.

final CreateTranscriptionRequest_model model = new CreateTranscriptionRequest_model(); // CreateTranscriptionRequest_model |

final String prompt = new String(); // String | An optional text to guide the model's style or continue a previous audio segment. The [prompt](/docs/guides/speech-to-text/prompting) should match the audio language.

final String responseFormat = new String(); // String | The format of the transcript output, in one of these options: `json`, `text`, `srt`, `verbose_json`, or `vtt`.

final BigDecimal temperature = new BigDecimal(); // BigDecimal | The sampling temperature, between 0 and 1. Higher values like 0.8 will make the output more random, while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic. If set to 0, the model will use [log probability](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Log_probability) to automatically increase the temperature until certain thresholds are hit.

final array[String] timestampGranularitiesLeft_Square_BracketRight_Square_Bracket = new array[String](); // array[String] | The timestamp granularities to populate for this transcription. `response_format` must be set `verbose_json` to use timestamp granularities. Either or both of these options are supported: `word`, or `segment`. Note: There is no additional latency for segment timestamps, but generating word timestamps incurs additional latency.

Required

temperature
BigDecimal
The sampling temperature, between 0 and 1. Higher values like 0.8 will make the output more random, while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic.         ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        AudioApi apiInstance = new AudioApi();
        File file = BINARY_DATA_HERE; // File | The audio file object (not file name) translate, in one of these formats: flac, mp3, mp4, mpeg, mpga, m4a, ogg, wav, or webm.

        CreateTranscriptionRequest_model model = ; // CreateTranscriptionRequest_model | 
        String prompt = prompt_example; // String | An optional text to guide the model's style or continue a previous audio segment. The [prompt](/docs/guides/speech-to-text/prompting) should be in English.

        String responseFormat = responseFormat_example; // String | The format of the transcript output, in one of these options: `json`, `text`, `srt`, `verbose_json`, or `vtt`.

        BigDecimal temperature = 8.14; // BigDecimal | The sampling temperature, between 0 and 1. Higher values like 0.8 will make the output more random, while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic. If set to 0, the model will use [log probability](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Log_probability) to automatically increase the temperature until certain thresholds are hit.


        try {
            createTranslation_200_response result = apiInstance.createTranslation(file, model, prompt, responseFormat, temperature);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling AudioApi#createTranslation");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

var opts = {
  'prompt': prompt_example, // {String} An optional text to guide the model's style or continue a previous audio segment. The [prompt](/docs/guides/speech-to-text/prompting) should be in English.

  'responseFormat': responseFormat_example, // {String} The format of the transcript output, in one of these options: `json`, `text`, `srt`, `verbose_json`, or `vtt`.

  'temperature': 8.14 // {BigDecimal} The sampling temperature, between 0 and 1. Higher values like 0.8 will make the output more random, while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic. If set to 0, the model will use [log probability](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Log_probability) to automatically increase the temperature until certain thresholds are hit.

};

var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.createTranslation(file, model, opts, callback);

from __future__ import print_statement
import time
import openapi_client
from openapi_client.rest import ApiException
from pprint import pprint

# Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
openapi_client.configuration.access_token = 'YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN'

# Create an instance of the API class
api_instance = openapi_client.AudioApi()
file = BINARY_DATA_HERE # File | The audio file object (not file name) translate, in one of these formats: flac, mp3, mp4, mpeg, mpga, m4a, ogg, wav, or webm.
 (default to null)
model =  # CreateTranscriptionRequest_model |  (default to null)
prompt = prompt_example # String | An optional text to guide the model's style or continue a previous audio segment. The [prompt](/docs/guides/speech-to-text/prompting) should be in English.
 (optional) (default to null)
responseFormat = responseFormat_example # String | The format of the transcript output, in one of these options: `json`, `text`, `srt`, `verbose_json`, or `vtt`.
 (optional) (default to json)
temperature = 8.14 # BigDecimal | The sampling temperature, between 0 and 1. Higher values like 0.8 will make the output more random, while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic. If set to 0, the model will use [log probability](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Log_probability) to automatically increase the temperature until certain thresholds are hit.
 (optional) (default to 0)

try:
    # Translates audio into English.
    api_response = api_instance.create_translation(file, model, prompt=prompt, responseFormat=responseFormat, temperature=temperature)
    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:
    print("Exception when calling AudioApi->createTranslation: %s\n" % e)
extern crate AudioApi;

pub fn main() {
    let file = BINARY_DATA_HERE; // File
    let model = ; // CreateTranscriptionRequest_model
    let prompt = prompt_example; // String
    let responseFormat = responseFormat_example; // String
    let temperature = 8.14; // BigDecimal

    let mut context = AudioApi::Context::default();
    let result = client.createTranslation(file, model, prompt, responseFormat, temperature, &context).wait();

    println!("{:?}", result);
}

Parameters

Form parameters
Name Description
file*
File (binary)
The audio file object (not file name) translate, in one of these formats: flac, mp3, mp4, mpeg, mpga, m4a, ogg, wav, or webm.
Required
model*
CreateTranscriptionRequest_model
Required
prompt
String
An optional text to guide the model's style or continue a previous audio segment. The [prompt](/docs/guides/speech-to-text/prompting) should be in English.
response_format
String
The format of the transcript output, in one of these options: `json`, `text`, `srt`, `verbose_json`, or `vtt`.
temperature
BigDecimal
The sampling temperature, between 0 and 1. Higher values like 0.8 will make the output more random, while lower values like 0.2 will make it more focused and deterministic. If set to 0, the model will use [log probability](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Log_probability) to automatically increase the temperature until certain thresholds are hit.

        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class

        try {
            CreateEmbeddingResponse result = apiInstance.createEmbedding(createEmbeddingRequest);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {

            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

namespace Example
{
    public class createEmbeddingExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
            Configuration.Default.AccessToken = "YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN";

            // Create an instance of the API class
            var apiInstance = new EmbeddingsApi();
            var createEmbeddingRequest = new CreateEmbeddingRequest(); // CreateEmbeddingRequest | 

            try {
                // Creates an embedding vector representing the input text.
                CreateEmbeddingResponse result = apiInstance.createEmbedding(createEmbeddingRequest);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            } catch (Exception e) {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling EmbeddingsApi.createEmbedding: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

Files

createFile

Upload a file that can be used across various endpoints. The size of all the files uploaded by one organization can be up to 100 GB. The size of individual files can be a maximum of 512 MB or 2 million tokens for Assistants. See the [Assistants Tools guide](/docs/assistants/tools) to learn more about the types of files supported. The Fine-tuning API only supports `.jsonl` files. Please [contact us](https://help.openai.com/) if you need to increase these storage limits. 


/files

import java.io.File;

public class FilesApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        FilesApi apiInstance = new FilesApi();
        File file = BINARY_DATA_HERE; // File | The File object (not file name) to be uploaded.

        String purpose = purpose_example; // String | The intended purpose of the uploaded file.

Use "fine-tune" for [Fine-tuning](/docs/api-reference/fine-tuning) and "assistants" for [Assistants](/docs/api-reference/assistants) and [Messages](/docs/api-reference/messages). This allows us to validate the format of the uploaded file is correct for fine-tuning.


        try {
            OpenAIFile result = apiInstance.createFile(file, purpose);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling FilesApi#createFile");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.FilesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class FilesApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        FilesApi apiInstance = new FilesApi();
        String fileId = fileId_example; // String | The ID of the file to use for this request.

        try {
            'String' result = apiInstance.downloadFile(fileId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling FilesApi#downloadFile");

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class

        try {
            ListFilesResponse result = apiInstance.listFiles(purpose);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling FilesApi#listFiles");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import java.io.File;

public class FineTuningApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        FineTuningApi apiInstance = new FineTuningApi();
        String fineTuningJobId = ft-AF1WoRqd3aJAHsqc9NY7iL8F; // String | The ID of the fine-tuning job to cancel.


        try {
            FineTuningJob result = apiInstance.cancelFineTuningJob(fineTuningJobId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling FineTuningApi#cancelFineTuningJob");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import org.openapitools.client.*;
import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;
import org.openapitools.client.api.FineTuningApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class FineTuningApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        FineTuningApi apiInstance = new FineTuningApi();
        String after = after_example; // String | Identifier for the last job from the previous pagination request.
        Integer limit = 56; // Integer | Number of fine-tuning jobs to retrieve.

        try {
            ListPaginatedFineTuningJobsResponse result = apiInstance.listPaginatedFineTuningJobs(after, limit);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling FineTuningApi#listPaginatedFineTuningJobs");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

};

  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.listPaginatedFineTuningJobs(opts, callback);

            var limit = 56;  // Integer | Number of fine-tuning jobs to retrieve. (optional)  (default to 20)

import org.openapitools.client.auth.*;
import org.openapitools.client.model.*;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ImagesApiExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        ImagesApi apiInstance = new ImagesApi();
        File image = BINARY_DATA_HERE; // File | The image to edit. Must be a valid PNG file, less than 4MB, and square. If mask is not provided, image must have transparency, which will be used as the mask.
        String prompt = prompt_example; // String | A text description of the desired image(s). The maximum length is 1000 characters.
        File mask = BINARY_DATA_HERE; // File | An additional image whose fully transparent areas (e.g. where alpha is zero) indicate where `image` should be edited. Must be a valid PNG file, less than 4MB, and have the same dimensions as `image`.
        CreateImageEditRequest_model model = ; // CreateImageEditRequest_model | 
        Integer n = 56; // Integer | The number of images to generate. Must be between 1 and 10.
        String size = size_example; // String | The size of the generated images. Must be one of `256x256`, `512x512`, or `1024x1024`.
        String responseFormat = responseFormat_example; // String | The format in which the generated images are returned. Must be one of `url` or `b64_json`. URLs are only valid for 60 minutes after the image has been generated.
        String user = user_example; // String | A unique identifier representing your end-user, which can help OpenAI to monitor and detect abuse. [Learn more](/docs/guides/safety-best-practices/end-user-ids).


        try {
            ImagesResponse result = apiInstance.createImageEdit(image, prompt, mask, model, n, size, responseFormat, user);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ImagesApi#createImageEdit");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
        HttpBearerAuth ApiKeyAuth = (HttpBearerAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("ApiKeyAuth");
        ApiKeyAuth.setBearerToken("BEARER TOKEN");

        // Create an instance of the API class
        ImagesApi apiInstance = new ImagesApi();
        File image = BINARY_DATA_HERE; // File | The image to use as the basis for the variation(s). Must be a valid PNG file, less than 4MB, and square.
        CreateImageEditRequest_model model = ; // CreateImageEditRequest_model | 
        Integer n = 56; // Integer | The number of images to generate. Must be between 1 and 10. For `dall-e-3`, only `n=1` is supported.
        String responseFormat = responseFormat_example; // String | The format in which the generated images are returned. Must be one of `url` or `b64_json`. URLs are only valid for 60 minutes after the image has been generated.
        String size = size_example; // String | The size of the generated images. Must be one of `256x256`, `512x512`, or `1024x1024`.
        String user = user_example; // String | A unique identifier representing your end-user, which can help OpenAI to monitor and detect abuse. [Learn more](/docs/guides/safety-best-practices/end-user-ids).


        try {
            ImagesResponse result = apiInstance.createImageVariation(image, model, n, responseFormat, size, user);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ImagesApi#createImageVariation");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Api;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Client;
using Org.OpenAPITools.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class retrieveModelExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            // Configure Bearer access token for authorization: ApiKeyAuth
            Configuration.Default.AccessToken = "YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN";

            // Create an instance of the API class
            var apiInstance = new ModelsApi();
            var model = gpt-3.5-turbo;  // String | The ID of the model to use for this request (default to null)

            try {
                // Retrieves a model instance, providing basic information about the model such as the owner and permissioning.
                Model result = apiInstance.retrieveModel(model);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            } catch (Exception e) {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling ModelsApi.retrieveModel: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

extern crate ModelsApi;

pub fn main() {
    let model = gpt-3.5-turbo; // String

    let mut context = ModelsApi::Context::default();
    let result = client.retrieveModel(model, &context).wait();

    println!("{:?}", result);
